<TITLE> RAB nabs drug peddler </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 2 (bdnews24.com)  RAB members Saturday arrested a 55-year-old woman in Bagbari area under Mirpur Police Station allegedly for selling narcotics. The elite force also seized 100 grams of heroin and Tk 5,000 from her. RAB officer flight lieutenant Mostafa Humayun Kabir told bdnews24.com that they caught Shova Adhikari as she was selling heroin to two youths. Shova admitted that she had long been selling drugs in Dhaka and areas closy-by. Kabir said they turned her in to Mirpur police Saturday evening. bdnews24
